## REQUIREMENTS - Kubernetes Best Practices

### 1. Deployment Manifest
**MUST Include:**
- Proper metadata (name, labels, annotations)
- Replica count (minimum 2 for availability)
- Update strategy (RollingUpdate with maxSurge/maxUnavailable)
- Pod template with proper labels
- Security context (run as non-root user)
- Resource requests and limits (CPU, memory)
- Liveness and readiness probes
- Proper container image with tag (never :latest)
- Environment variables and configuration
- Graceful termination (terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 30)

**Security Context Requirements:**
```yaml
securityContext:
  runAsNonRoot: true
  runAsUser: 1000
  runAsGroup: 1000
  fsGroup: 1000
  capabilities:
    drop:
      - ALL
  readOnlyRootFilesystem: false  # Set true if app supports it
  allowPrivilegeEscalation: false
```

**Resource Management:**
- Set realistic CPU and memory requests based on application needs
- Set limits to prevent resource exhaustion
- Use appropriate QoS class (Burstable or Guaranteed)

**Health Probes:**
- Liveness probe: Detects if application is dead (restart on failure)
- Readiness probe: Detects if application can serve traffic
- Startup probe: For slow-starting applications (optional)
- Use httpGet for HTTP apps, tcpSocket for TCP, or exec for custom checks

### 2. Service Manifest
**MUST Include:**
- Proper metadata (name, labels)
- Selector matching Deployment labels
- Service type (ClusterIP for internal, LoadBalancer for external)
- Port mapping (port, targetPort, protocol)
- Session affinity if needed

### 3. Labels & Annotations
**Standard Labels (app.kubernetes.io):**
- app.kubernetes.io/name: Application name
- app.kubernetes.io/instance: Deployment instance name
- app.kubernetes.io/version: Application version
- app.kubernetes.io/component: Component role
- app.kubernetes.io/part-of: Part of larger system
- app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: Tool managing the resource

**Useful Annotations:**
- prometheus.io/scrape: "true" (if metrics available)
- prometheus.io/port: Metrics port
- prometheus.io/path: Metrics endpoint path

